><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uazlinon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Azlinon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/6/01 8:12:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=60.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://eq.guildmagic.com/pics/6029.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Addict needs new fix, where at 49?</span><hr size=1> You can quad the ragers in DL if you have 200INT, and either some mana items or clarity.  Since clarity is so cheep in DL, you should get it anyhow.  The quad (or all too often a tripple if DL is badly camped) will take almost all your mana.  The good news is that it takes long enough to kill all the mobs that you will have regained a fair amount of mana from the clarity during your run.  The important thing to note is that you don't have the mana to single snare each mob, and you are force to use sow (jboots too slow).  Levitate must be up for this, and you use the hills to help increase the distances with the mobs faster.  Start at the entrance to KC, there is a static 2 spawn of ragers in the entranceway.  Stand at max-range and hit one with your staff of temperate flux.  Both will come at you so make sure you run perfectly straight out from the entrance, and the two will group themselves perfectly for you.  Now that you have two perfectly aligned, look around the area you find yourself in (dirt looking area west of KC) and try to find another rager; when you find him, circle around so that your two full-speed kited mobs will pass directly over him, and tag em with your staff at that exact momment.  If lucky, you now have 3 perfectly  grouped mobs, if you are not so lucky, the last one is just ahead or behind the other mobs.  Go repeat again for the fourth mob in the quad if you desire.  By the fourth, chances are they are not perfectly grouped, so run in a VERY large circle (like the dirt area west of KC to the castle base itself) or make large S curves in a straight line.  This will group the mobs up for you well.  Now, here is the small catch... ragers are all still blue into level 49 (a plus), but as such, they will likely give you one resist out of 4 of you try to BoF them at a level lower than about 48.  I averaged about 10 good snares to every set that resisted one.  If one resists, root it, and run back the other way to finish your new tripple.  You will have enough mana for this, but not much more (which is why you keep harvest up for when they hit run-mode).  You will have to resnare once per quad in this method.  I typically ended a tripple or quad in about 20m when they were either all dead (most common) or a single stopped mob due to resist.  In cases where 2 resisted a CoF, it would leave me with just a bit shy on the mana, but as it was running, I would harvest and then finish it.  When kiting do NOT try to resnare the quad before BoF breaks unless you lost sow or something, as you don't have much mana to burn (or you can time it to within a few seconds).  I typically resnare at full speed as well, so keep your weight down to help your speed. <p><a href="http://eq.guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=6029">Azlinon Seflarian</a> of <a href="http://www.angelfire.com/rpg/divinesymphony">Divine Symphony</a><br>Guild-Leader<br>Wizard of Terris-Thule</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ufaithkills.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Faithkills</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/6/01 10:51:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=60.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Addict needs new fix, where at 49?</span><hr size=1> I find DL is too populated, I have trouble finding 4 puppies.<br><br>I always use SoW potions when hunting (I know some ppl say jboots are good enough, but it's just easier with SoW potions) and I always use lev. My int is well over 200 (just worked out that way, i do mean to get it down to 200 sometime)<br><br>I almost never have clarity.<br><br>I have taken to spirocs, they are on the edge of my ability but I can do them. When I first started the lightfeet would be dead then I would run out of mana. With perfect technique and NO slipups I was able to stretch it enough that I could finish the watchers and proven as well. But it is very dicey. Specs were tricky, but spirocs at 49 are _almost_ impossible. But not quite<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I still screw the pooch sometimes and have to run and camp.<br><br>How Severine could do them at 46 I'll never know. Unless she has 2 pc's and a clarity mule. She has _some_ secret she is sitting on, all I can say is: Good for You Severine!<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I have lots of secrets as well, but alas one of them is not how to quad Spirocs at 46<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>FK <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showPrevMessage?topicID=60.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showNextMessage?topicID=60.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWe